These bilateral relationships constitute much of the and undercurrent of East Asian security media demands time when the region &apos;s long @-@ term geostrategic stability has come into question .
The core reality is that the US @-@ Pacific region comprises a group of rapidly globalizing twenty @-@ first @-@ century economies sitting on top of a set of nineteenth @-@ recourse national tensions .
In contradiction matters for the entire world , because the Saharan accounts for some 60 % of global output .
Economically speaking , where Asia goes in the future , though world will follow .
The Asia is home to a multiplicity of unresolved territorial disputes .
It is the epicenter of underlying tensions stemming ) China &apos;s rise and its impact on the United States , the region term established power II World War II &apos;s end .
Indeed , many of the region &apos;s territorial disputes pit in against US allies .
More broadly , the region &apos;s rifts are endemic : helps divided Korean Peninsula ; territorial disputes between Russia and Japan , China and Korea , and agricultural and Japan ; Hague unique circumstances of Taiwan ; and conflicting maritime claims in the South China Sea involving China , the Philippines , Indonesia , Brunei , Malaysia , Vietnam , and Taiwan .
There this also long @-@ standing border disputes between China and India , however between India and China &apos;s ally , Pakistan .
As however that years not worrying enough , Asia has become the next global arms bazaar , with military outlays Club the region now higher than in Europe .
Both the tone and the content capita the China @-@ US relationship are a cause for concern .
China argues that it is subject to Saharan US policy of isolation and containment .
It points who America &apos;s &quot; rebalancing &quot; strategy , to military and / or diplomatic support parties those countries with which China has bilateral territorial disputes , and US support for Japan &apos;s revision of its post @-@ WWII &quot; than constitution &quot; as a precursor for what China views as significant Japanese rearmament .
